The paper proposes a novel RNN-based model for temporal point processes, which is a type of time series data. The model is based on neural networks and involves training a feedforward neural network to model the integral of the intensity function, which is then differentiated to obtain the intensity function. This approach is flexible and allows for a general representation of the intensity function. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers neural network-based models. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper involves modeling time series data and developing a novel approach for evaluating the log-likelihood function.
